\title{Motivation of a group}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-17}
\taxon{remark}

\p{The whole motivation for a group is to describe symmetries, which was usually described using a [[gr-004Y]]. The first application was to study the symmetries of polynomials in an attempt to find roots of polynomials, which culminated in Galois theory.}